  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients undergoing primary multi-vessel CABG with at least two saphenous vein grafts,
             with or without the use of cardiopulmonary bypass.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Emergency surgery

          -  Valve surgery

          -  Redo CABG

          -  Left ventricle ejection fraction &lt; 30%

          -  Preoperative use of clopidogrel (with the exception of the current admission)

          -  Preoperative use of warfarin

          -  Allergy to aspirin or clopidogrel

          -  History of cerebrovascular accident

          -  History of severe liver disease

          -  Morbid obesity

          -  Current malignancy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
